<div class="problem"><p>A matrix $A$ is idempotent if $A^2=A$.  Show that the only possible eigenvalues of an idempotent matrix are $\lambda=0$ and $\lambda=1$.  Then give an example of a matrix that is idempotent and has both of these two values as eigenvalues.
